640
00:37:41.148 --> 00:37:44.308
cancer, and I have no conflicts to disclose.

641
00:37:45.028 --> 00:37:48.188
So dedifferentiated endometrial cancer, and we've seen this picture in the

642
00:37:48.208 --> 00:37:48.828
introduction,

643
00:37:49.668 --> 00:37:53.248
is a histopathology that's characterized by the

644
00:37:54.728 --> 00:37:58.668
well-differentiated areas that are in juxtaposition to very poorly

645
00:37:58.708 --> 00:38:02.108
differentiated areas. Now due to this rapid

646
00:38:02.128 --> 00:38:06.068
morphological change, it's theorized that these types of malignancies

647
00:38:06.108 --> 00:38:09.728
are occurring via stochastic mechanism, most likely a

648
00:38:09.748 --> 00:38:10.428
mutation.

649
00:38:11.748 --> 00:38:15.348
Now DDEC, in contrast to endometrial cancers in general,

650
00:38:16.188 --> 00:38:19.808
has a very, very poor prognosis. Over 80% of

651
00:38:19.868 --> 00:38:23.128
patients with DDEC will progress and succumb to their

652
00:38:23.188 --> 00:38:26.928
disease. This is characterized by extensive metastases as well as

653
00:38:26.948 --> 00:38:28.288
resistance to therapies.

654
00:38:29.428 --> 00:38:33.258
And it highlights the need to better understand the process by which these cells

655
00:38:33.288 --> 00:38:35.918
become dedifferentiated and enable progression.

656
00:38:37.068 --> 00:38:40.428
So to do this, we think of this cancer within an epigenomic

657
00:38:40.528 --> 00:38:44.488
context and relating it to development into embryonic

658
00:38:44.548 --> 00:38:48.448
stem cells. So in this particular cartoon, we can see embryonic

659
00:38:48.508 --> 00:38:52.368
stem cells on the left-hand side, and what would be our DDECs

660
00:38:52.428 --> 00:38:56.228
on the right-hand side. As we discussed in the introduction, during

661
00:38:56.248 --> 00:39:00.068
development, or when we're doing directed differentiation,

662
00:39:00.648 --> 00:39:04.248
in response to factors in the microenvironment, embryonic stem cells are

663
00:39:04.288 --> 00:39:06.828
gradually specified to the various tissues in the body.

664
00:39:07.188 --> 00:39:09.088
And so in terms of this, it would be the

665
00:39:10.088 --> 00:39:11.168
epithelium within the

666
00:39:12.868 --> 00:39:13.328
uterus.

667
00:39:14.548 --> 00:39:18.408
We think that during cancer, this can be undone, leading to these very

668
00:39:18.448 --> 00:39:21.968
embryonic-like phenotypes, and that it's very likely that this is due to a

669
00:39:21.988 --> 00:39:25.408
mutation. I'll highlight some similarities and differences.

670
00:39:25.448 --> 00:39:28.578
So one is in the microenvironment and features that may help to promote this

671
00:39:28.648 --> 00:39:32.378
dedifferentiation. This can include features such as low oxygen or

672
00:39:32.408 --> 00:39:36.268
hypoxia, which has been shown to both enhance induced pluripotency,

673
00:39:36.968 --> 00:39:40.388
as well as the acquisition of stem-like phenotypes and dedifferentiation in a

674
00:39:40.408 --> 00:39:44.368
variety of cancers. I'll also highlight a major difference with that.

675
00:39:44.428 --> 00:39:47.528
On this side, we have a case that's highly unregulated.

676
00:39:47.588 --> 00:39:51.548
So while these cells may display an embryonic-like phenotype, they're really

677
00:39:51.608 --> 00:39:55.017
unable to get cues from the microenvironment and to properly

678
00:39:55.228 --> 00:39:59.168
redifferentiate. And that's of course, in contrast to the stem cells, which yes,

679
00:39:59.228 --> 00:40:02.988
can self-renew, but then also can listen to their microenvironment to

680
00:40:03.028 --> 00:40:04.948
execute appropriate programming.

681
00:40:06.428 --> 00:40:09.788
And so we were really asking the question as to what kinds of

682
00:40:09.808 --> 00:40:13.628
mutations may actually be driving this dedifferentiation in

683
00:40:13.688 --> 00:40:17.568
these endometrial cancers. And so this work was initiated by Mackenzie

684
00:40:17.608 --> 00:40:21.388
Cotham here in close collaboration with two pathologists, Changhon

685
00:40:21.428 --> 00:40:24.648
Lee and Martin Koebel, at the University of Alberta in Calgary.

686
00:40:25.828 --> 00:40:29.438
And so what was done initially was to take these lesions, and to

687
00:40:29.438 --> 00:40:33.028
microdissect the adjacent regions, and then to compare the

688
00:40:33.068 --> 00:40:35.928
well-differentiated components to the dedifferentiated components

